OL,4,CBank chair
OL,6,FA number of preliminary hearings in
OL,7,Fthe case were previously aborted when
OL,8,FFlowers cited health problems, and in
OL,9,FNovember 2023 another crown court
OL,10,Fjudge issued a similar warrant when
OL,11,FFlowers did not appear as scheduled.
OL,13,FJudge Dean noted the defendant had
OL,14,F"fragile mental health" but that an
OL,15,Fimmediate custodial sentence could be
OL,16,F"almost inevitable" for an offence
OL,17,Fover a sustained period involving a
OL,18,F"vulnerable victim", which he said may
OL,19,Fexplain why the defendant had not
OL,20,Fattended.
